&lt;h1 id="how-to-think-for-yourself"&gt;How to Think for Yourself&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are some kinds of work that you can&amp;rsquo;t do well without thinking differently from your peers. To be a successful scientist, for example, it&amp;rsquo;s not enough just to be correct. Your ideas have to be both correct and novel. You can&amp;rsquo;t publish papers saying things other people already know. You need to say things no one else has realized yet.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Read What You Love Until You Love to Read</title><link>https://linguista.cn/person/naval/orig/read-what-you-love-until-you-love-to-read/</link><pubDate>Wed, 03 Apr 2019 11:37:49 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguista.cn/person/naval/orig/read-what-you-love-until-you-love-to-read/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://linguista.cn/person/naval/zh/read-what-you-love-until-you-love-to-read.zh/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
